Questions:
What is the primary goal of the research study titled "Improving the Patient Experience During Bone Marrow Biopsy/Aspiration (BMBA): Do Interventions Decrease Distress and Pain"?
A) To compare the effectiveness of different bone marrow biopsy techniques;
B) To assess the impact of various relaxation and distraction methods on patient experience during bone marrow biopsies;
C) To determine the accuracy of bone marrow biopsy results;
D) To evaluate the long-term outcomes of patients after bone marrow biopsies.

Correct answer: B) To assess the impact of various relaxation and distraction methods on patient experience during bone marrow biopsies.

If you choose to withdraw from the study early, what will be expected of you?
A) You will be required to pay a penalty fee for early withdrawal;
B) You will be asked to complete some of the procedures described in the consent form, such as the post-procedure survey;
C) You will have to provide a detailed explanation for your decision to withdraw;
D) You will be obligated to continue participating in other unrelated studies.

Correct answer: B

If you experience a research-related injury during the study, whom should you inform as soon as possible?

A) Your primary care physician;
B) The main investigator, Anne Delengowski, or investigator Michelle Lasota;
C) The emergency room staff only;
D) Your insurance company.

Correct answer: B) The main investigator, Anne Delengowski, or investigator Michelle Lasota.
